        "title": "How to pass companion object output in Kotlin as parameter in object creation in Java?",
        "body": "<p>I am using Kotlin library to my java android project\nKotlin lib. have 2 classes <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class MyClass1{\n  constructor(param1 ,param2,param3){}\n   public companion object {\n     val S1= MyClass1(param1,param2,param3)\n     val S2= MyClass1(param1,param2,param3)\n   }\n}\n\n\nclass MyClass2 {\n (private var loc: Location?, private var method: MyClass1?)\n} \n\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I need to pass S1 or S2 to constructor of MyClass2 in Java<\/p>\n\n<p><code>MyClass2 newClass= MyClass2(loc, MyClass1.S1);<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>I found that I should use Companion before S1 , but I got error => Method call expected<\/p>\n",
